// Framework — Modules domain: module config, bindings, engagement stats.
//
// Fork-owned (Daybreak), not Sunrise. Per the boundary convention in
// `.context/framework/planning/framework-architecture.md` Appendix B (X6):
// every table here uses the `framework_` prefix via `@@map`, and its DDL lands
// only in `framework_`-named migrations touching only `framework_*` tables.
// Prisma model names stay clean/unprefixed (e.g. `model Module { @@map("framework_module") }`).
//
// First table (f-module-core t-1). See `.context/framework/planning/f-module-core.md`
// and spec §4.1.

// A registered module's operator-controlled row. The code half (identity, config
// schema, capabilities…) lives in a `ModuleDefinition` registered in code; this row
// holds only what an operator controls. Registration syncs code → row by slug at
// boot (`syncRegisteredModules()`), which writes code-owned data on create and only
// re-marks `isRegistered` on update — operator columns are never clobbered.
//
// `status`/`audience` are free-form `String`, not Prisma enums (convention X1: an
// enum makes every new value a migration and complicates fork merges). Effective
// availability is COMPUTED, never stored (`isModuleLive()` — status × flag × window,
// f-module-core t-2); this row stores the inputs, not the verdict.
//
// Scope note: config *versioning* (`ModuleVersion`, A10 → f-module-config) and the
// binding pivots (agents/workflows, A6/A8 → f-module-bindings) are intentionally
// absent — added by the features that own them, so no unused columns land early.
model Module {
  id              String    @id @default(cuid())
  slug            String    @unique // matches the registered ModuleDefinition.slug
  name            String // display name; defaults from code, operator-overridable
  status          String    @default("draft") // draft | active | scheduled | retired (free-form, X1)
  featureFlagName String? // optional binding to a FeatureFlag (one on/off switch)
  availableFrom   DateTime? // limited-time window start (null = open-ended)
  availableUntil  DateTime? // limited-time window end (null = open-ended)
  audience        String    @default("all") // all | invite | flag-gated (free-form, X1)
  config          Json      @default("{}") // operator values, validated by the module's configSchema (f-module-config)
  isRegistered    Boolean   @default(true) // false = code removed but row retained for audit
  createdAt       DateTime  @default(now())
  updatedAt       DateTime  @updatedAt

  @@index([status])
  @@map("framework_module")
}
